Put chicken into the crock of a slow cooker. Stir cayenne pepper sauce and ranch dressing mix together in a bowl until smooth; pour over chicken. Cook on Low for 6 to 7 hours. Transfer chicken to a large bowl and use 2 forks to shred chicken into strands. Strain liquid from slow cooker crock into a bowl to serve on the side. Spoon chicken into lettuce leaves and roll lettuce around chicken.